itt於1433年出生在英國林可爾史爾凱特萊比時，他的父親Adam Tyrwhitt39歲，母親Elizabeth Lumley45歲。他於1455年與Jane Waterton結婚。他們至少是1個兒子的父母。他在英國越可爾被列為high sheriff 。他去世於大約1458年4月23日在他的家鄉享年25歲。"},"zh-hans":{"1433–about 23 April 1458":"1433年–大约1458年4月23日","1433–1458":"1433年–1458年","1435–1461":"1435年–1461年","1456–1522":"1456年–1522年","1395–1451":"1395年–1451年","1389–1462":"1389年–1462年","1462":"1462年","1451":"1451年","1395":"1395年","1461":"1461年","after 24 April 1418":"1418年4月24日之后","about 23 April 1458":"大约1458年4月23日","1458":"1458年","1435":"1435年","1522":"1522年","1456":"1456年","1433":"1433年","1455":"1455年","1389":"1389年","about 1456":"大约1456年","about 1451":"大约1451年","Kettleby, Lincolnshire, England":"英国林可爾史爾凱特萊比","England":"英国","Lincolnshire, England":"英国林可爾史爾","lifeSummary":"当Sir Robert Tyrwhitt于1433年出生在英国林可爾史爾凱特萊比时，他的父亲Adam Tyrwhitt39岁，母亲Elizabeth Lumley45岁。他于1455年与Jane Waterton结婚。他们至少是1个儿子的父母。他在英国越可爾被列为high sheriff 。他去世于大约1458年4月23日在他的家乡享年25岁。"},"hr":{"1433–about 23 April 1458":"1433.–oko 23. travnja 1458.","1433–1458":"1433.–1458","1435–1461":"1435–1461","1456–1522":"1456–1522","1395–1451":"1395–1451","1389–1462":"1389–1462","1462":"1462","1451":"1451","1395":"1395","1461":"1461","after 24 April 1418":"nakon 24. travnja 1418.","about 23 April 1458":"oko 23. travnja 1458.","1458":"1458","1435":"1435","1522":"1522","1456":"1456","1433":"1433.","1455":"1455.","1389":"1389","about 1456":"oko 1456.","about 1451":"oko 1451.","Kettleby, Lincolnshire, England":"Kettleby, Lincolnshire, England","England":"England","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"},"cs":{"1433–about 23 April 1458":"1433–okolo 23. dubna 1458","1433–1458":"1433–1458","1435–1461":"1435–1461","1456–1522":"1456–1522","1395–1451":"1395–1451","1389–1462":"1389–1462","1462":"1462","1451":"1451","1395":"1395","1461":"1461","after 24 April 1418":"po 24. dubna 1418","about 23 April 1458":"okolo 23. dubna 1458","1458":"1458","1435":"1435","1522":"1522","1456":"1456","1433":"1433","1455":"1455","1389":"1389","about 1456":"okolo 1456","about 1451":"okolo 1451","Kettleby, Lincolnshire, England":"Kettleby, Lincolnshire, Anglie","England":"Anglie","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Anglie"},"da":{"1433–about 23 April 1458":"1433–omkring 23. april 1458","1433–1458":"1433–1458","1435–1461":"1435–1461","1456–1522":"1456–1522","1395–1451":"1395–1451","1389–1462":"1389–1462","1462":"1462","1451":"1451","1395":"1395","1461":"1461","after 24 April 1418":"efter 24. april 1418","about 23 April 1458":"omkring 23. april 1458","1458":"1458","1435":"1435","1522":"1522","1456":"1456","1433":"1433","1455":"1455","1389":"1389","about 1456":"omkring 1456","about 1451":"omkring 1451","Kettleby, Lincolnshire, England":"Kettleby, Lincolnshire, England","England":"England","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"},"nl":{"1433–about 23 April 1458":"1433–circa 23 april 1458","1433–1458":"1433–1458","1435–1461":"1435–1461","1456–1522":"1456–1522","1395–1451":"1395–1451","1389–1462":"1389–1462","1462":"1462","1451":"1451","1395":"1395","1461":"1461","after 24 April 1418":"na 24 april 1418","about 23 April 1458":"circa 23 april 1458","1458":"1458","1435":"1435","1522":"1522","1456":"1456","1433":"1433","1455":"1455","1389":"1389","about 1456":"circa 1456","about 1451":"circa 1451","Kettleby, Lincolnshire, England":"Kettleby, Lincolnshire, England","England":"England","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"},"en":{"1433–about 23 April 1458":"1433–about 23 April 1458","1433–1458":"1433–1458","1435–1461":"1435–1461","1456–1522":"1456–1522","1395–1451":"1395–1451","1389–1462":"1389–1462","1462":"1462","1451":"1451","1395":"1395","1461":"1461","after 24 April 1418":"after 24 April 1418","about 23 April 1458":"about 23 April 1458","1458":"1458","1435":"1435","1522":"1522","1456":"1456","1433":"1433","1455":"1455","1389":"1389","about 1456":"about 1456","about 1451":"about 1451","Kettleby, Lincolnshire, England":"Kettleby, Lincolnshire, England","England":"England","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Tyrwhitt","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Trewhitt  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Trewhitt","meanings":["English (Durham and Yorkshire): habitational name from High and Low Trewhitt in Rothbury (Northumberland). The origin of the placename is uncertain. This name has sometimes been confused with   Trevett  ."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":22,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Robert Tyrwhitt was born in 1433, in Kettleby, Lincolnshire, England, his father, Adam Tyrwhitt, was 39 and his mother, Elizabeth Lumley, was 45. He married Jane Waterton in 1455. They were the parents of at least 1 son. His occupation is listed as high sheriff  in Yorkshire, England. He died about 23 April 1458, in his hometown, at the age of 25."},"et":{"1433–about 23 April 1458":"1433–umbes 23. aprill 1458","1433–1458":"1433–1458","1435–1461":"1435–1461","1456–1522":"1456–1522","1395–1451":"1395–1451","1389–1462":"1389–1462","1462":"1462","1451":"1451","1395":"1395","1461":"1461","after 24 April 1418":"pärast 24. aprilli 1418","about 23 April 1458":"umbes 23. aprill 1458","1458":"1458","1435":"1435","1522":"1522","1456":"1456","1433":"1433","1455":"1455","1389":"1389","about 1456":"umbes 1456","about 1451":"umbes 1451","Kettleby, Lincolnshire, England":"Kettleby, Lincolnshire, England","England":"England","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"},"fi":{"1433–about 23 April 1458":"1433–noin 23. huhtikuuta 1458","1433–1458":"1433–1458","1435–1461":"1435–1461","1456–1522":"1456–1522","1395–1451":"1395–1451","1389–1462":"1389–1462","1462":"1462","1451":"1451","1395":"1395","1461":"1461","after 24 April 1418":"24. huhtikuuta 1418 jälkeen","about 23 April 1458":"noin 23. huhtikuuta 1458","1458":"1458","1435":"1435","1522":"1522","1456":"1456","1433":"1433","1455":"1455","1389":"1389","about 1456":"noin 1456","about 1451":"noin 1451","Kettleby, Lincolnshire, England":"Kettleby, Lincolnshire, England","England":"England","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England"},"fr":{"1433–about 23 April 1458":"1433–environ 23 avril 1458","1433–1458":"1433–1458","1435–1461":"1435–1461","1456–1522":"1456–1522","1395–1451":"1395–1451","1389–1462":"1389–1462","1462":"1462","1451":"1451","1395":"1395","1461":"1461","after 24 April 1418":"après 24 avril 1418","about 23 April 1458":"environ 23 avril 1458","1458":"1458","1435":"1435","1522":"1522","1456":"1456","